column5: Made it out after some lakers this week...freezing cold both times and was only out for about an hour and a half each time but we managed these two lakers, just under 4lbs and 7lbs respectively...My buddy also landed a nice pike in the process.
Nice looking fish, how deep were you finding them?
they were down around 15-20 feet over 25-30 FOW...check out my blog for more details; lure selection, speed, etc.  http://ontariooutdoors.weebly.com/
Great stuff!  This report is becoming a regular thing every year
